        "explanation": "Aripiprazole, ziprasidone, and lurasidone are considered metabolically favorable — they have minimal effects on weight, glucose, and lipids. Clozapine and olanzapine carry the highest metabolic risk (weight gain, new-onset diabetes). Quetiapine has moderate-to-high metabolic risk. Metabolic monitoring (weight, waist circumference, fasting glucose, lipids) is recommended for all antipsychotics, but especially for higher-risk agents."
