        "explanation": "Aripiprazole (partial D2 agonist) can cause impulse control disorders — gambling, hypersexuality, compulsive eating — by partial dopamine agonism in reward pathways. This is a class effect of dopamine partial agonists (also seen with pramipexole in Parkinson's). The FDA added a black box warning in 2016. Dose reduction or discontinuation typically resolves the behavior."
