        "explanation": "When converting from sublingual asenapine to Secuado, the bioavailability is approximately equivalent (the patches are calibrated to deliver comparable systemic exposure to the SL formulations). The conversion is dose-matched: 5 mg SL BID → 3.8 mg/24hr patch; 10 mg SL BID → 7.6 mg/24hr patch."
