        "explanation": "Fluoxetine's activating/energizing profile (partly due to 5-HT2C antagonism and noradrenergic effects) can cause initial anxiety, agitation, and insomnia at treatment start. Patients should be warned that this usually resolves within 1–2 weeks. Starting at low doses (10 mg) and dosing in the morning can minimize this."
